<P><b>Equiprobable Spaces</b>  
<BR>Here the outcomes of the Sample Space are assigned equal probabilities.
<P><b>Example</b>
<Br>In throwing a fair die:
<Br>
<img src="Image29.png">
<Br>Let the event A be defined by "getting at least a 5 on a single throw".   Then A = {5, 6}.
<UL>Pr(A) = n(A)/n(S) = 2/6 = 1/3</UL>
<P><b>Example</b>
<P>Determine the probability of selecting a spade from a set of 52 cards.
<Br>Event A = {card is a spade}
<Br>Pr(A) = n(A)/n(S) = 13/52 = 1/4

